{"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"overlayBounds","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","roleHeading":"Instance Property","symbolKind":"property","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS","iPadOS","Mac Catalyst"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readonly","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310).","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"title":"MLNOverlay"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","kind":"symbol","title":"MapLibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"title":"overlayBounds"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCoordinateBounds":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncoordinatebounds","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNCoordinateBounds","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A rectangular area as measured on a two-dimensional map projection."}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"identifier"}]}}}